item.description:
Dom Dolla "Tomorrowland Adscendo, A Digital Introduction [Belgium, 28.1.2023.]"
Dolby Atmos Music



Dominic Matheson, better known by his stage name Dom Dolla, is an Australian house music producer, songwriter and remixer, acclaimed for his distinct style of house music and high-profile collaborations. Grammy Award nominee in 2024 for the song "New Gold", featuring Gorillaz, Tame Impala, & Bootie Brown. Juno Award nominee in 2024 for the song "Eat Your Man", featuring Nelly Furtado. Has been nominated eight times for the ARIA Award for Best Dance Release; Including: in 2017 for "Be Randy", with Torren Foot and in 2019, for the song "Take It". He won the award at the 2020 ARIA Music Awards for the song "San Frandisco" and in 2023 for the song "Rhyme Dust" (with MK). Performed in festivals such as Coachella 2022 and Lollapalooza 2023. Dom has sold out such venues as Red Rocks Amphitheatre in Denver, Colorado, Sidney Myer Music Bowl in Melbourne, Australia and Forest Hills Stadium in New York.
